{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=o|おう}}
{{IPAchar|/apu/}} → {{IPAchar|/afu/}} → {{IPAchar|/au/}} → {{IPAchar|/ɔː/}} → {{IPAchar|/oː/}}

From {{der|ja|ltc|-}} {{ltc-l|凹}}. Compare modern {{cog|cmn|-}} reading ''āo'', {{cog|nan|-}} ''au''.

{{ja-noun|くぼ}}

# an area with sides higher than the center: an [[indentation]], a [[depression]], a [[dip]], a [[divot]], a [[hole]]
# {{lb|ja|sort=くぼ|slang}} female [[genitalia]], the [[vagina]]

{{der-top|Terms derived from {{lang|ja|凹}} (''kubomi'')}}
* {{ja-r|凹 石|くぼみ いし}}, {{ja-r|窪 石|くぼみ いし}}: an [[artifact]] from the [[w:Jōmon_period|Jōmon period]], consisting of a flat stone with one to several indentations, of uncertain utility but thought to be used to help start fires
{{der-bottom}}

{{ja-noun|なかくぼ}}

# a [[sunken]] [[center]]
# a [[place]] or [[object]] with a sunken center

* {{sense|hollow}} {{ja-r|窪み|くぼみ}}, {{ja-r|窪|くぼみ}}, {{ja-r|凹み|くぼみ}}, {{ja-r|凹|くぼみ}} (''also see above'')
* {{sense|mistake}} {{ja-r|失%策|しっ%さく}}
* {{sense|mistake}} {{ja-r|失%敗|しっ%ぱい}}
* {{sense|at a loss}} {{ja-r|困%惑|こん%わく}}

{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|ぼこ}}
Uncertain. Possibly [[onomatopoeic]] from the sound of a wheel bouncing in a rut or pothole, or from the sound of something hollow when tapped. Compare adverb {{m|ja|ぼこぼこ|tr=bokoboko||full of holes; hollowly}}.

Alternately, may be compound of {{compound|ja|sort=ほこ'|ぼ|tr1=bo|t1=empty?|pos1=uncertain; possibly related to verb {{m|ja|掘る|tr=horu||to dig, to dig out}}|こ|tr2=ko|t2=place|pos2=suffixing element seen in other words such as {{m|ja|そこ|tr=soko||there}} or {{m|ja|端っこ|tr=hashikko||edge, end, tip}}}}. Compare {{m|ja|凸|tr=deko||protrusion}}, likely a compound of {{m|ja|出|tr=de||coming out}} + {{m|ja|こ|tr=ko||place|pos=suffixing element}}.

{{der-top|Terms derived from {{lang|ja|凹}} (''boko'')}}
* {{ja-r|ぼこぼこ|ぼこぼこ}}: [[unevenly]], [[bumpily]], [[pitted]], [[dented]] (in multiple places), [[full]] of [[hole]]s; [[hollowly]]
{{der-mid}}
* {{ja-r|穴ぼこ|あなぼこ}}: a [[hole]], a [[rut]], a [[pothole]]
* {{ja-r|凸%凹|でこ%ぼこ}}: [[unevenness]], [[bumpiness]], [[jaggedness]]; [[inequality]], [[disparity]]
{{der-bottom}}
